         <abstract>
            <p>Different sets of conditions for an estimate of the form $$\|y - y^\pi\|_{L_\infty(a,b)} \leqslant C \operatornamewithlimits{\max}_i h^{r+1}_i\|y^{(r+1)}\|_{L_\infty(I_i)}$$ to hold are given. Here, $y^\pi$ is the Galerkin approximation to the solution $y$ of a boundary value problem for an ordinary differential equation, the trial functions being polynomials of degree $\leqslant r$ on the subintervals $I_i = \lbrack x_i, x_{i+1} \rbrack$ of length $h_i$. The sequence of subdivisions $\pi: x_0 &lt; x_1 &lt; \cdots &lt; x_n$ need not be quasi-uniform.</p>
          </abstract>
